docs.abstract: O’Rourke gave Texans who have long felt disenfranchised a glimpse of what could be.
docs.snippet: O’Rourke gave Texans who have long felt disenfranchised a glimpse of what could be.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — The condolence emails are already coming in, from New York, and California, and from my neighbors down the street, who are mostly limiting themselves to unprintable but predictable four-letter words. Yes, Beto O’Rourke lost to Ted Cruz, 51-48 percent, an outcome that surprised almost no seasoned politicos around these parts — they’ve been predicting it for months, some since the congressman from El Paso first announced his candidacy last year. Rest assured that the Monday-morning quarterbacking will proceed apace starting … now.
